##  Key Design Decisions

* Modular architecture for scalability
* Clean separation of frontend, backend, and AI services
* Structured REST APIs
* Database optimized for research paper management
* Responsive user experience with intuitive navigation
* Scope aligned with the approved MVP

##  Key Learnings

* A strong system design reduces implementation complexity.
* Defining APIs early improves frontend and backend collaboration.
* Database planning prevents future structural changes.
* Wireframing helps validate user experience before coding.
* Clear project structure makes development more maintainable.

##  Outcome

The complete technical blueprint for PaperLens is now finalized. With architecture, APIs, schema, UI, and project organization documented, the project is ready to move into the implementation phase.
